bloodhound watches the /etc/master.passwd and /var/db/data/*, and updates an RDF
database in /var/db/meta when those files change. bloodhound depends on Python,
rdflib, and Berkley DB.


Contents of this distribution:

    Makefile        full installation instructions

    README          this file

    bloodhound.1    manual page

    bloodhound.py   script itself

    setup.py        Python installation script


To install:

    % cd ~
    % svn export http://www.zetadev.com/svn/public/bloodhound/trunk bloodhound
    % cd svneol
    % make install


To uninstall:

    % cd ~/bloodhound
    % make uninstall
